Web Developer
- ,
Date Posted: 2014/05/06 11:54:26
Ref. JB3047883
Job Description
SAG Off Shore Lebanon is currently looking for a web developer. The position entails the development, maintenance and administration of both the frontend and backend of a bilingual (English and Arabic) social-based web platform.
Applicants should be familiar with open source software, standards and the latest web technologies and protocols. Initially, applicants will be required to familiarize themselves with the platform’s existing CMS framework for a set period of time.
Responsibilities include:
•	Web application development, and maintenance
•	Responsible for the evaluation, testing, implementation, and customization of open source components, modules, and plug-ins
•	Supporting and maintaining existing applications and user interfaces
•	Ensuring that all development work is following standards and best practices
•	Other duties as assigned
Skills
•	College degree in IT or equivalent
•	Knowledge in Python
•	Knowledge in building websites and applications using the Django framework
•	Fluency in Linux, CSS, HTML, JavaScript, JQuery, Ajax, Postgresql and Nginx.
•	A passion for the user experience and interface
•	Self-motivated with interest in learning new applications and systems
•	Ability to work in a development team
This job is posted in the following Specialties:
Education
IT or equivalent
